  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "An 18-month-old boy presents to the emergency department 2 hours after injuring himself while playing with his older sister. He tripped while running and hit the side of his face against the corner of a table. He is alert and crying.\nHe has a 1.5-cm laceration through the lower vermilion border of his lip. The laceration does not extend to the wet mucosal surface of the lower lip, and no other facial or dental trauma is evident. The margins appear to be clean, and there is minimal bleeding.\nWhich one of the following initial steps should be taken to ensure successful repair of this patient's laceration?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Plan for delayed closure of the wound"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Irrigate the wound with hydrogen peroxide"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Plan for procedural sedation"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Apply a coolant spray to the site"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Administer a dose of amoxicillin-clavulanate"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Zd8520929eef4b367e8b8b5d54c0b0870\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Zd8520929eef4b367e8b8b5d54c0b0870\" data-section-id=\"jqX_y_\" data-sememe-id=\"V2bGgG\">Primary closure</a> is preferred for lip <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"UlWbwl0\">lacerations</a>. Delayed closure may be indicated for infected wounds (for example, a heavily soiled wound or a wound from a significant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ds0oFh&anker=Z8dc1d59d7e2230a539d199a8dc746ce1\" data-learningcard-id=\"ds0oFh\" data-anker=\"Z8dc1d59d7e2230a539d199a8dc746ce1\">animal bite</a>) or in patients at increased risk for infection, such as in cases of presentation to medical care after 24 hours.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>The wound should be irrigated with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=fM0kLg&anker=Zca7fd28598a951a5b85443bbe965acd0\" data-learningcard-id=\"fM0kLg\" data-anker=\"Zca7fd28598a951a5b85443bbe965acd0\" data-section-id=\"kdcmJY0\" data-sememe-id=\"wWbhns\">normal saline</a> before closure. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WQ0PEf&anker=Z79cc6a035f0231d13df11645a78b175c\" data-learningcard-id=\"WQ0PEf\" data-anker=\"Z79cc6a035f0231d13df11645a78b175c\" data-section-id=\"Y4cn3c0\">Antiseptics</a> such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WQ0PEf&anker=Z6476a9fe9de22677ae624486e3f917b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"WQ0PEf\" data-anker=\"Z6476a9fe9de22677ae624486e3f917b1\" data-section-id=\"Y4cn3c0\" data-sememe-id=\"bccHaY0\">hydrogen peroxide</a> can be cytotoxic and cause tissue injury. Although <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WQ0PEf&anker=Z79cc6a035f0231d13df11645a78b175c\" data-learningcard-id=\"WQ0PEf\" data-anker=\"Z79cc6a035f0231d13df11645a78b175c\" data-section-id=\"Y4cn3c0\">antiseptics</a> may be used to cleanse wounds in other parts of the body, they should be avoided in lip and mouth <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"UlWbwl0\">lacerations</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"UlWbwl0\">Lacerations</a> are a leading cause of visits to the emergency department. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z60632b64136794064c681e545906a186\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z60632b64136794064c681e545906a186\" data-section-id=\"fv1kzi0\" data-sememe-id=\"gtXF1-\">vermilion border</a>, which is the junction of the dry oral <span data-sememe-id=\"Ze1Zxf0\">mucosa</span> and the facial <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a>, is a structure whose misalignment by even 1 mm can cause a noticeable <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Za55944151461e1f8e8c40b24592110d5\" data-section-id=\"ZvXZA-\">scar</a> with significant cosmetic effects.<br><br>Preparing the patient for wound closure is of utmost importance to relieve the patient’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kP0mUT&anker=Z6ed492871b68b31189bcb84adbfe1e96\" data-learningcard-id=\"kP0mUT\" data-anker=\"Z6ed492871b68b31189bcb84adbfe1e96\">anxiety</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>. Not all patients require <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=w70hLh&anker=Z4a8ccabda9c4d013fbd3c182f91efdaf\" data-learningcard-id=\"w70hLh\" data-anker=\"Z4a8ccabda9c4d013fbd3c182f91efdaf\" data-sememe-id=\"kFcmRV0\">procedural sedation</a>, but it facilitates repair in very young, anxious, or uncooperative children who require precise approximation, such as for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"UlWbwl0\">lacerations</a> of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z60632b64136794064c681e545906a186\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z60632b64136794064c681e545906a186\" data-section-id=\"fv1kzi0\" data-sememe-id=\"gtXF1-\">vermilion border</a>. In this patient, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=w70hLh&anker=Z4a8ccabda9c4d013fbd3c182f91efdaf\" data-learningcard-id=\"w70hLh\" data-anker=\"Z4a8ccabda9c4d013fbd3c182f91efdaf\" data-sememe-id=\"kFcmRV0\">procedural sedation</a> would optimize the likelihood of a cosmetically appealing result.<br><br><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wN0hWg&anker=Z644811627a57e3dfe4a14ee195a02cbf\" data-learningcard-id=\"wN0hWg\" data-anker=\"Z644811627a57e3dfe4a14ee195a02cbf\">Local anesthetics</a> may be used for cooperative patients. A regional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sl0ywT&anker=Z005a641786ea9ef3d6131d6b9c8262ea\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sl0ywT\" data-anker=\"Z005a641786ea9ef3d6131d6b9c8262ea\" data-section-id=\"pNcLX10\" data-sememe-id=\"53biQt\">nerve block</a> of the infraorbital and mental nerves is another excellent <span data-sememe-id=\"hj1cZS0\">anesthetic</span> method for lip <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"UlWbwl0\">laceration</a> repair. If the lip injury or tissue loss is extensive, a plastic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a> consultation is a reasonable option, but it is not required for the repair described in this case.<br><br>All patients with lip injuries should also be evaluated for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=is0Juh&anker=Z3cf3c8cd054e4f51121ccde33ea7a608\" data-learningcard-id=\"is0Juh\" data-anker=\"Z3cf3c8cd054e4f51121ccde33ea7a608\" data-section-id=\"KWWUm40\">dental trauma</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ct0qf3&anker=Zffa89b0fcdc479035a5c17b25b050a0c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ct0qf3\" data-anker=\"Zffa89b0fcdc479035a5c17b25b050a0c\" data-section-id=\"_pW5Hm0\">mandibular fractures</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=eR0xNf&anker=Zeeea010691e509dc2b3dce3821f08877\" data-learningcard-id=\"eR0xNf\" data-anker=\"Zeeea010691e509dc2b3dce3821f08877\" data-section-id=\"opa0ql\" data-sememe-id=\"Je1s-f0\">closed head injuries</a>.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> The repair of a lip <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"UlWbwl0\">laceration</a> that extends through the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jp0_6S&anker=Z60632b64136794064c681e545906a186\" data-learningcard-id=\"jp0_6S\" data-anker=\"Z60632b64136794064c681e545906a186\" data-section-id=\"fv1kzi0\" data-sememe-id=\"gtXF1-\">vermilion border</a> in a <span data-sememe-id=\"gQWFvO0\">toddler</span> is best facilitated with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=w70hLh&anker=Z4a8ccabda9c4d013fbd3c182f91efdaf\" data-learningcard-id=\"w70hLh\" data-anker=\"Z4a8ccabda9c4d013fbd3c182f91efdaf\" data-sememe-id=\"kFcmRV0\">procedural sedation</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Topical sprays should not be applied to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z37717da933761c4bc6ea84ca86e900ef\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z37717da933761c4bc6ea84ca86e900ef\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"HG1K0i0\">open wounds</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>In general, facial <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"UlWbwl0\">lacerations</a> do not require any <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z59b09641b101520dcac91806ce3bc6c4\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z59b09641b101520dcac91806ce3bc6c4\" data-section-id=\"cubaJv\" data-sememe-id=\"Ydbnos\">antibiotic prophylaxis</a>. Large lip <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"UlWbwl0\">lacerations</a> that extend into the wet <span data-sememe-id=\"Ze1Zxf0\">mucosa</span> of the lip or those that are the result of an <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ds0oFh&anker=Z8dc1d59d7e2230a539d199a8dc746ce1\" data-learningcard-id=\"ds0oFh\" data-anker=\"Z8dc1d59d7e2230a539d199a8dc746ce1\">animal bite</a> may require a prophylactic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotic</a> that covers oral flora (such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z90b22a582dd430878a33b6cf97fd0d4f\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z90b22a582dd430878a33b6cf97fd0d4f\" data-section-id=\"jRc_5X0\" data-sememe-id=\"UOab7k\">penicillin</a>, <span data-sememe-id=\"lIdv1r0\">amoxicillin-clavulanate</span>, or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-section-id=\"ijcJZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"HOaKFk\">clindamycin</a>). Simple lip <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z0e098a92252f6708b918be9f7214b8c0\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"UlWbwl0\">lacerations</a> generally require application of topical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a>, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z37ca24e10ca3a6835fd4b232402957e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z37ca24e10ca3a6835fd4b232402957e6\" data-section-id=\"djcozX0\" data-sememe-id=\"OyXI200\">bacitracin</a>, to the external wound after closure.</div>",
      "hint": "",
